Cell.Text: Well, that's a ridiculous question. Everyone traveling through here has said that the Oblivion Gates have been opening all over Tamriel.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQSaintDremoraBranchTopic: Why would a dremora attack you?

Cell.Text: Has it been that long? Oh my. | Well, it started with the followers of Mehrunes Dagon having Emperor Uriel Septim VII assassinated. | Without a Septim on the throne of the Empire, Dagon was able to leave Oblivion through the gates and attack.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQSaintDremoraBranchTopic01: That was... a bit before my time.

Cell.Text: All I heard is that without a Septim sitting on the throne of the Empire, the Dragonfires in a place called the Temple of the One were no longer lit. | This meant that we were vulnerable to the forces of Oblivion.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQSaintDremoraBranchTopic02: Why was Dagon able to do this?

Cell.Text: [S] Well, I don't know. Everything seemed fine until that dremora attacked me. I only heard later about the gates from the other souls. | I can only assume the gates have been closed by now.
I had just moved from my ancestral home in Morrowind to the continent of Cyrodiil. | I settled in the city of Kvatch to write my memoirs and to find some peace and quiet.
Ah, yes. Saint Jiub, Jiub the Eradicator, Jiub the Magnificent... I've earned a lot of those titles thanks to my campaign against the Winged Menace.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQSaintJiubHistoryBranchTopic: How did you earn your nicknames?

Cell.Text: Yes. I'm speaking of the Cliff Racer of course. Wretched things. | They used to criss-cross the skies over Morrowind like vermin. Nasty flying creatures with a habit of sneaking up on the unwary.

[S] After I was freed from prison, I decided to turn my life around. Give something back to the people of Morrowind. | It became quickly apparent that the best way I could help would be by wiping out the cliff racers.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQSaintJiubHistoryBranchTopic02: What was your campaign against them?

Cell.Text: Indeed I was. I hunted down and killed every last one of them. Took years. | The people of Morrowind were so grateful to have the roads safer again, they took to calling me "Saint Jiub" and then the other names followed.
That was a dark time in my life. I did a lot of things I ended up regretting. | Maybe that's why I worked so hard to redeem myself once I was freed.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQSaintPrisonBranchTopic: You said you were in prison?

Cell.Text: I murdered others for money. And before you think I belonged to some romantic or secretive guild, think again. | I was simply an addict who needed money for skooma. The stuff wasn't cheap, and murder always seemed to be in demand.
I finally bit off more than I could chew. | I was paid to assassinate some high-ranking official from House Redoran. | What I didn't know is someone had hired the Morag Tong to kill him as well.

Exactly. | He got to my target first and called the guard to cover his tracks. By the time I got there, the place was on alert. | Walked right into a trap, and didn't even realize it until I was captured.
They tried me for murder, threw me on a prison ship and sent me to the jail in Vivec City. | Gave me a lot of time to think, that's for sure.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQSaintPrisonBranchTopic04: So what ended up happening to you?

Cell.Text: Indeed! One moment I was writing diligently, and the next, my door bursts open. | It was a cadre of dremora. The city was under attack. | I took it upon myself to join the cause and fight the dremora, thinking this would simply be another feather in my cap.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQSaintHomeBranchTopic01: Is that where you were attacked?

Cell.Text: The reason I'm standing in front of you as only a whisper of my former self should tell you that. | I never knew what became of Kvatch. I wonder if they were triumphant without me.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQSaintHomeBranchTopic02: Didn't work out that way I assume.
